    • Method Detail

      • connect

        public void connect(java.lang.String uri)
             throws java.net.URISyntaxException
        Connects to a server by specifying its URI and creates a new instance of oneM2M services. Examples:
        • connect("coap://192.168.0.104:5685/augmented-things"); connects the client to the infrastructure ADN at the address 192.168.0.104
        • connect("coap://192.168.0.105:5684/~/augmented-things-MN-cse"); connects the client to the middle-node CSE at the address 192.168.0.105:5684
        Parameters:
        uri - the server URI
        Throws:
        java.net.URISyntaxException - URI is not valid

      • connect

        public void connect(java.lang.String uri,
                    boolean createService)
             throws java.net.URISyntaxException
        Connects to a server by specifying its URI. Examples:
        • connect("coap://192.168.0.104:5685/augmented-things"); connects the client to the infrastructure ADN at the address 192.168.0.104
        • connect("coap://192.168.0.105:5684/~/augmented-things-MN-cse"); connects the client to the middle-node CSE at the address 192.168.0.105:5684
        Parameters:
        uri - the server URI
        createService - specifies whether creating a new instance of oneM2M services or not
        Throws:
        java.net.URISyntaxException - URI is not valid
